In [88]:
plt.figure(figsize=[4, 6], dpi=150)
y = [num ** 2 + num - 12 for num in x] # y = x**2 + x - 12
y1 = [num + 10 for num in x] # y1 = x + 10

# plot number 1 - to show the quadratic equation
plt.plot(x, y, label="quadratic", color="orange", linestyle='dashed') ##0ba9e3

# plot number 2 - to show the linear equation
plt.plot(x, y1, label="linear", color="#E18898", linestyle='solid',
        marker='.', markersize=10, markeredgecolor = '#163EEA') #e3940b


plt.title("Quadratic vs Linear",
         fontdict={"fontname":"Comic Sans MS",
                  "fontsize":20})

plt.xlabel("X Axis",
          fontdict={"fontname":"Comic Sans MS",
                  "fontsize":15})

plt.ylabel("Y Axis",
          fontdict={"fontname":"Comic Sans MS",
                  "fontsize":15})

plt.legend() # show the labels that have been set on the plt.plot
plt.show()

In [191]:
def categorize_weights(weight):
    if weight > 50 and weight <= 60 :
        return "light"
    elif weight > 60 and weight <= 70 :
        return "medium light"
    elif weight > 70 and weight <= 80 :
        return "medium"
    elif weight > 80 and weight <= 90 :
        return "medium heavy"
    else:
        return "heavy"
